cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with querying objects described by a tree-structured ontology, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The focus on semantic searches and interpretations also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The development of algorithms and lower bounds for finding top-k similar pairs of objects falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
